I don&#39;t think its the only legitimate way to do it, but it is the most easily unquestionable way to do it.  I still hold on to the idea that if you can get your sweep speed measurement you can find a way to legitimize communication on variou speeds.  However, that&#39;s not nearly as easy and surefire as simply setting your speed so fast that it is categorically unquestionable, if you have a radio with adjustable speed.  I don&#39;t think a fast speed is a detriment to hearing them.  If they want to come through and communicate they seem to be able to find a way to do it at both faster and slower speeds, from what I&#39;ve seen so far.  You simply have to keep your ears open to new sounds.  When you begin communicating at a speed you&#39;ve never used before, I would suggest asking them questions that require predictable answers like yes/no, days of the week, months, colors, etc. so you have an approximate idea what to listen for... 


